results.name: Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=2} log(k)/(k^2-1).
formula: Equals Sum_{i>=1} -zeta'(2i) = A073002 + A261506 - Sum_{i>=3} zeta'(2i).
Sum_{k>=2} log(k)/(k^2-s) = -Sum_{i>=1} s^(i-1)*zeta'(2i) for |s|<4. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 03 2021
